The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 December is 12,826 (1,484.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 December, there were 1,788 new confirmed cases (206.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 December, there were 907 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 97% (881 extra cases).
